‘I’m not going!’ he screams at me as the game resumes behind us. ‘My team
was winning! I scored the first goal!’
‘I saw that and it was a great goal but it’s getting dark. Wila is freezing and
you’ve both got homework to do.’
‘But we always have to go straight home! How come the others are alowed to
play? I’m sick of stupid homework! I’m sick of always being at home!’
