family to look after, this place gives me peace. It gives me hope. In summer
it’s lovely here. It silences the roar that’s constantly in my head . . .
‘Maybe, from time to time, this could be your place too,’ I suggest quietly.
‘Everyone needs time off, Lochan. Even you.’
He nods again, stil looking around, as if trying to imagine me here by myself.
Then he turns back to me, the colar of his black jacket flapping against his
