children’s ward. Head lowered, he is leaning forward on his hands, gripping
the edge of a windowsil.
‘Lochie!’
He whirls round as if struck, straightens up slowly, then approaches me
rapidly, raising his hands as if in surrender.
‘She’s fine, she’s fine, she’s absolutely fine – they gave her a sedative and gas
and air for the pain and were able to push the bone straight back in. I’ve just
